    "This can be represented as where MLP and MLP are multi-layer perceptron parameterized by trainable parameters and, respectively.",
    "Node-level aggregation is a common approach that combines information from neighboring nodes to compute representations for individual nodes.",
    "This method treats nodes as unstructured entities and does not explicitly consider the graph structure during aggregation.",
    "On the other hand, graph-level aggregation takes into account the local structural information during the aggregation process.",
    "It goes beyond simple node-level aggregation and considers the relationships and connectivity between nodes to perform higher-order graph aggregation."
